<p>Bildquelle: Dragino Technology Co. </p>","","","0","a:3:{i:0;s:19:\"158462408729.02.jpg\";i:1;s:25:\"158462408729.02_thumb.jpg\";i:2;s:0:\"\";}","a:3:{i:0;N;i:1;N;i:2;s:0:\"\";}","a:3:{i:0;N;i:1;N;i:2;s:0:\"\";}","a:3:{i:0;N;i:1;N;i:2;s:0:\"\";}","Permanent-Monitoring","<p>Our aim is to provide a product for professional pest control operator (PCO) that enables following advantages for himself and his customers:</p>
<ul>
<li>Reduction of inspection intervals, because only \"visited\" bait stations have to be checked.</li>
<li>Saving of time takes place through less effort of control - time can be used for other jobs and activities: increase in turnover.</li>
<li>Exact proof within documentation, which bait station was “visited” during what time and how often.</li>
<li>Competitive advantage, thereby increase customer loyalty.</li>
<li>Boxes can be placed in sensitive sectors.</li>
<li>Inspection of live traps is only necessary if infestation exists.</li>
<li>IFS-, BRC- und AIB-conformable.</li>
<li>Implementation of the risk mitigation measures for rodent control</li>
</ul>
<p>Very important: <a href=\"http://permanentmonitoring.frowein808.de/home/?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">HYGiTEC<sup>®</sup> Permanent-Monitoring</span></a> can be used autarchic, i.e. HYGiTEC<sup>®</sup> Documentation-System is not a precondition.</p>
<p><strong>PRINCIPLE AND FUNCTION</strong></p>
<p>The rodent monitors (specially preinstalled mouse and rat bait stations and also live traps) are equipped with an electronic motion detector that transfers thermal motions in the bait stations wireless by radio to a data receiver. The range amounts about 100 meters in open field which can be extended and adapted to the environment by a special technology.</p>
<p>The “visited” bait station is identified by the code (e.g. a bar code) and is marked as “active”.</p>
<p>Thus, you can act on each real infestation message immediately and follow them purposefully in each individual case.</p>
<p><strong>Overview of the individual modules:</strong></p>
<p><strong><img src=\"/uploads/136681093524.15.jpg\" alt=\"\" /> <img src=\"/uploads/GSMBlackbox_Aufsatzmodul_mit_Antennen%202_21.02.2013_5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"225\" height=\"150\" /></strong></p>
<p style=\"text-align: left;\"> </p>
<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Yellow = GSM-antenna. Red = Receives the signals<br />GSM-modem sends the of the sending units<br />received data via (bait stations).<br />this antenna to the PCO.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>GSM-box:</strong></p>
<p>For data-reception of the respective sending units and data-transmission to the PCO. With an integrated GSM-modem (SIM-card). The data card is provided by the PCO. A connection via WLAN is planned in future. Power supply 230 V.</p>
<p><img src=\"/uploads/Sendeeinheit_Aufsatzmodul%201_18.01.2013.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"205\" height=\"120\" /> <img src=\"/uploads/Sendeeinheit_Aufsatzmodul%202_18.01.2013.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"177\" height=\"120\" /></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Sending unit:</strong></p>
<p>Reports infestation by motion and warmth, transfers data to the GSM-box. Power supply by two lithium batteries, type AA (not included). Assuming that each bait station/sending unit sends 30 seconds per day, the battery life time is approx. 1 year. That is a very pessimistic scenario, so that a duration of more than 2 years might be possible.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><img src=\"/uploads/Repeater%201_18.01.2013.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"206\" /></p>
<p><strong>Repeater:</strong></p>
<p>Receives the signal of the sending units, amplifies this and transfers it to the GSM-box. If necessary, several repeaters (any number) can be connected in series. The needed socket can be used again.</p>
<ul>
<li>Description:</li>
</ul>
<p>The development and production is in Germany. Only components of very high quality are used.</p>
<p>Addressing of each sending unit is performed via IPv6. Therefore, every sending unit has its own ID (MAC-address). This remains when replacing the battery. This results that at first installation, all sending units automatically log-in at the GSM-box and don’t have to be registered separately with the software (technical term: autopairing). According to that, an extension of an existing installation is also very simple.</p>
<p>Each sending unit reports a status message within a freely definable interval (e.g. 24 h). With every status message, the actual battery status is reported, too. This ensures that the PCO is informed anytime about the functionality of the system and can react immediately on a possible component failure.</p>
<p>All the system parameters (e.g. intervals of the status message) can be modified on the new GSM-box and then automatically transferred to all boxes.</p>
<p>The sending unit needs two lithium batteries of type „AA\" (not included). Assuming that each bait station/sending unit sends 30 seconds per day, the battery life is approx. 1 year. That is a very pessimistic scenario, so that battery service lives of over 2 years are possible.</p>
<p>Therefore, e.g. if live traps are used, the system can be configured in that way that there are waiting periods, when a sending unit triggers a signal after umpteenth time that within a certain period, it doesn’t trigger again, to save battery life. The new GSM-box sends data via an integrated GSM-modem (SIM-card), like the version before. Prospects: data transmission via WLAN or via SMS are planned in future.</p>
<p>SMS has the advantage that data can be send even when the reception strength of the data network is absolutely bad.</p>
<p>Further information:</p>
<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><a href=\"http://permanentmonitoring.frowein808.de/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">http://permanentmonitoring.frowein808.de/</span></a></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Further relevant features of the system:</li>
</ul>
<p>The radio range from the sending unit to GSM-box is approx. 100 m under optimal conditions (depending on the structure of the building).</p>
<p>No maximum number of possible sending units per GSM-box</p>
<p style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">* Any number of repeaters can be connected in series.</p>
<p style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">* Each sending unit on the bait station can also work as a repeater. But this should only be used in case of necessity, as it certainly consumes battery power. But in cases without power supply, it’s very helpful.</p>
<p style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">* Housing of the sending units are protected IP65.</p>
<p style=\"margin-left: 30px;\">* The housings are filled with synthetic resin, so that theoretically exist a protection class of IP67.</p>
<p>Repeater for outdoors available (protection class IP67).</p>","","","<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Ein softwarebasiertes System zur Überwachung von Schadnagerbefall. Die Nagermonitore sind speziell ausgestattete Mäuse- und Rattentunnel mit Schlagfallensystem, die mit Magnete und einer Sendeeinheit ausgestattet sind. Sobald der Magnetkontakt unterbrochen ist, meldet die Sendeeinheit per LoRa-Funktechnologie ein Signal an die Gateway.</span></p>
<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Die Gateway wird mit einem integriertem Modem und einer Multiband SIM-Karte ausgeliefert.</span></p>
<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Die Multiband SIM-Karte sucht sich automatisch den besten Netzanbieter aus und funktioniert länderübergreifend. Hierdurch wird die Meldung an den Server übermittelt und kann Online abgerufen und eine Benachrichtigung per SMS oder E-Mail konfiguriert werden.<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Gebrauchsmuster Nr. 20 2006 002 386.0, eingetragen am 29.6.2006 beim Deutschen Patentamt in München.</span><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">IPC: A01M 25/00 (2006.01)</span><br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Bezeichnung: Köderstation für schädliche Kleintiere, insbesondere Nager.</span></span></p>","<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Software-based module for monitoring rodent infestation</span></p>
