INSERT INTO newsletter_letters VALUES("181","2016-02-15 09:19:52","7","2","2","181","2011-11-11","\"808\" receives the first biocidal approvals according to Directive 98/8/EC","<p>Applications for rodenticides containing the active ingredient Difethialone had to be submitted before 1st November 2009 (29th November 2009 in Germany). Afterwards followed the two-year examination procedure (defined by the legislator) of the submitted documents. <strong>In good time before the deadline we received the registrations for our rodenticides Contrax-D Köder, Contrax-D Block 220, MausEX-D Block and MausEX-D Pad.</strong> These products for control of rodents can be marketed in Germany further on and can be used by the professional pest control operators for the effective rodent control. The registration numbers are: <strong>Contrax-D Köder: DE-2011-MA-14-00004-aa Contrax-D Block 220: DE-2011-MA-14-00002-aa MausEX-D Block: DE-2011-MA-14-00001-aa MausEX-D Pad: DE-2011-MA-14-00006-ab</strong> The registrations are limited to the 31st October 2014 and will be followed by a review (five year period from the date of application for registration). <strong>\"808\" - your choice for quality and safety.</strong> With best regards FROWEIN GMBH & CO. KG <strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Competence in Biocides - Solutions for Professionals</span></strong></p>","","0","","","","a:2:{i:16;s:1:\"1\";i:29;s:1:\"1\";}");
